    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a purist\u2019s build, powered by the S54B32 engine featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. It utilizes a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to send power through a factory M-Variable differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been executed, including rear subframe reinforcement and a dual-VANOS overhaul to ensure precise cam timing. The suspension geometry is sharp, aided by refreshed polyurethane control arm bushings. While the exterior displays light patina consistent with its 'good' status, the drivetrain remains robust and thermally efficient. This is a mechanically sound E46 ready for spirited canyon runs or daily engagement.",
